"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-andy-benesh-miles-partain-beach-volleyball-olympics-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"At the start of 2019, Andy Benesh was cold calling for a living, and Miles Partain was a high school junior.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This week, they mathematically clinched the first U.S. men's volleyball spot in the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 160, \"end\": 164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7112686015988046, \"rank\": 0.40593653076351705, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are ranked fourth in the world.\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh, 29, and Partain, 22, will be the youngest U.S. men's beach team in Olympic history (the sport debuted in 1996).\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 298, \"end\": 302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7112686015988046, \"rank\": 0.40593653076351705, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Partain will be the single youngest U.S. beach player in Olympic history, supplanting three-time gold medalist Misty May-Treanor, according to the OlyMADMen.\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 480, \"end\": 497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Misty_May-Treanor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Misty May-Treanor\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q15117302\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Misty_May-Treanor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Misty_May-Treanor\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TEAM USA:Athletes qualified for Paris Olympics  American men won three of the first four Olympic beach volleyball tournaments in 1996, 2000 and 2008.\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 528, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8989650816852968, \"rank\": 0.07780410723042522, \"text\": \"TEAM USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 560, \"end\": 574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 576, \"end\": 584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9954382530507825, \"rank\": 0.00456026743491141, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 625, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beach_volleyball\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.294189914514047e-30, \"text\": \"beach volleyball\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beach_volleyball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beach_volleyball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have not won a medal since.\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 710, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh finished his indoor college career at USC in 2017, played half a season with a balky back for a Swiss club, moved back to the U.S. and accepted a financial adviser job in March 2018.\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0017106193380554e-14, \"text\": \"USC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before passing the exams needed to start the gig, he began playing beach volleyball on the side.\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He finally started the job in September 2018, but quit by the following spring.\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1079, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"After about eight months of cold calling 300 people a day (without much success), I felt the spark inside me growing,\\\"Benesh wrote for AVP.com.\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1225, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I could not forget that feeling of qualifying (for tournaments), that desire to keep trying.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1319, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My boss encouraged our team members to show a motivational video at the beginning of every day to get people ready to cold call.\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One day, one of my colleagues showed a video from a famous entrepreneur named Gary Vaynerchuk.\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Vaynerchuk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gary Vaynerchuk\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Vaynerchuk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Vaynerchuk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, 'If you are looking forward to Friday and dreading Monday, you are not doing what you are meant to do.'\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That altered the direction of my life.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1695, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That single quote gave me the courage to tell my boss I did not enjoy any aspect of the job.\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When he replied, 'You are not supposed to,' - I quit.\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1842, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That wasn't going to be how I lived my life.\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1887, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With a bunch of student debt and almost no money to my name, I bet big on myself.\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was going to do everything I could to become a professional beach volleyball player.\\\"\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In November 2019, Benesh and Partain teamed in a one-off,winning a one-day Southern California tournament, when Partain was a high school senior and still playing indoors.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While Partain transitioned to UCLA, Benesh grinded professionally with seven different partners over the next three years.\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2354, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2262, \"end\": 2266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"score\": 0.9999999959172783, \"rank\": 3.948076847534669e-09, \"text\": \"UCLA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He did not forget about Partain, though.\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I always kind of knew I wanted to play with Miles,\\\" Benesh, a 6-foot-9 blocker,said on a USA Volleyball on a podcastpublished in February.\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sometimes you have just got to be patient.\", \"from\": 2537, \"to\": 2580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just knowing who he was, it was always in the back of my mind, maybe some day in the future it would happen.\\\"\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Partain was a promising prospect for years.\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At age 15, he became the youngest person to advance from qualifying into the main draw of a domestic AVP tournament, according to BVBinfo.com.\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So he had options when he decided as a college junior to follow his passion and go full-time to the beach.\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Partain had to leave UCLA's indoor program to do so in February 2023.\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3008, \"end\": 3012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"score\": 0.9999999959172783, \"rank\": 3.948076847534669e-09, \"text\": \"UCLA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Bruins won the program's 20th NCAA title without him three months later.\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3061, \"end\": 3067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"score\": 0.9999999928454599, \"rank\": 7.0119600456901515e-09, \"text\": \"Bruins\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\"}, {\"begin\": 3091, \"end\": 3095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9927602751154218, \"rank\": 0.007143656390275848, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You never know everything, but I really wanted to play with (Benesh),\\\"Partain said on the Sandcast podcast.\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's also kind of in my age bracket, sort of.\", \"from\": 3244, \"to\": 3290, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He went through the club scene, and then went to USC, sort of around when I was at UCLA.\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3340, \"end\": 3343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0017106193380554e-14, \"text\": \"USC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\"}, {\"begin\": 3374, \"end\": 3378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"score\": 0.9999999959172783, \"rank\": 3.948076847534669e-09, \"text\": \"UCLA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was before (I was at UCLA), but we can relate on a lot of that stuff.\\\"\", \"from\": 3380, \"to\": 3453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3404, \"end\": 3408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"score\": 0.9999999959172783, \"rank\": 3.948076847534669e-09, \"text\": \"UCLA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A year ago at this time, neither Benesh nor Partain had played a main-draw match in a top-level international tournament.\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In their debut on that stage last spring, they finished third.\", \"from\": 3578, \"to\": 3640, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The next one, they won.\", \"from\": 3641, \"to\": 3664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Between those two events, they beat each of the world's current top three teams (one via retirement from a set ahead).\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They defeated Tokyo Olympic gold medalists Anders Mol and Christian Sorum of Norway twice in one tournament, coming from a set down each time.\", \"from\": 3785, \"to\": 3927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3799, \"end\": 3804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999975872212421, \"rank\": 2.3037432245949387e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 3828, \"end\": 3838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anders_Mol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anders Mol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q15117302\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anders_Mol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anders_Mol\"}, {\"begin\": 3853, \"end\": 3858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sorum\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sorum\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sorum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sorum\"}, {\"begin\": 3862, \"end\": 3868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9981590303168366, \"rank\": 0.0018442376728844436, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like the world's top pair, 23-year-old Swedes David Ahman and Jonatan Hellvig, they have implemented therevolutionary jump setattack thatPartain has honed since his teens.\", \"from\": 3929, \"to\": 4100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Last year, our goal was just to be able to play against the best teams and play in the best tournaments in the world,\\\" Benesh said.\", \"from\": 4102, \"to\": 4234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Obviously, the Olympics is one of those.\\\"\", \"from\": 4235, \"to\": 4277, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Former NBA player Chase Budinger and Miles Evansare in the driver's seatfor the second and last possible U.S. men's team spot in Paris.\", \"from\": 4279, \"to\": 4414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4286, \"end\": 4289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.331776289405405e-12, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 4297, \"end\": 4311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Budinger\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chase Budinger\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Budinger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Budinger\"}, {\"begin\": 4408, \"end\": 4413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999978426786, \"rank\": 2.157455768036111e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The final tournament in qualifying is in early June.\", \"from\": 4415, \"to\": 4467, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The two U.S. women's teams previously clinched spots - 2023 World champions Kelly Cheng and Sara Hughes and Taryn Kloth and Kristen Nuss, who are ranked No.\", \"from\": 4469, \"to\": 4625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4545, \"end\": 4550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"score\": 0.992265791807803, \"rank\": 0.007794492419345601, \"text\": \"Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 4566, \"end\": 4572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"score\": 0.9999933114023358, \"rank\": 3.808668822946985e-06, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\"}, {\"begin\": 4593, \"end\": 4600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forrester_family\", \"score\": 0.9515057846079482, \"rank\": 0.05096575993195386, \"text\": \"Kristen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forrester_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forrester_family\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2 in the world.\", \"from\": 4626, \"to\": 4641, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 4645, \"to\": 4671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4645, \"end\": 4655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.999999998624844, \"rank\": 1.3751932130797453e-09, \"text\": \"A Division\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"DISCLAIMER: This site and the products offered are for entertainment purposes only, and there is no gambling offered on this site.\", \"from\": 4673, \"to\": 4803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This service is intended for adult audiences.\", \"from\": 4804, \"to\": 4849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No guarantees are made for any specific outcome.\", \"from\": 4850, \"to\": 4898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, please call 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 4899, \"to\": 4976, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u24b8 2024 NBC Universal\", \"from\": 4978, \"to\": 4998, \"entities\": []}]}"